-- Vietnam May Give Tax Preference to Businesses Conserving Energy
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-14T05:12:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/vietnam-may-give-tax-preference-to-businesses-conserving-energy.html
Vietnam ’s  finance ministry  will ask
Prime Minister Nguyen Tan Dung to give “some tax preference”
to businesses that have energy conservation plans or use so-
called green energy, Nguyen Van Phung, deputy director of  tax
policy  at the finance ministry, said today at a conference in
Hanoi.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
